          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best local SEO automation tool in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">theStacc is the best local SEO automation tool in 2026. It's the only tool that automates both GBP content (30 posts/month) AND blog content (30 articles/month) simultaneously. Start for $1, cancel anytime, first content publishes within 24 hours of signup.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What does local SEO automation actually mean?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">True local SEO automation means the tool does the work after setup — creates content, publishes posts, submits listings, responds to reviews, and tracks rankings on its own. Most tools marketed as automation are dashboards that monitor and wait for you to act. theStacc is one of the few that actually creates and publishes content without manual input.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What are the 5 pillars of local SEO that can be automated?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">The five pillars are: (1) GBP content automation, (2) blog content automation, (3) citation management, (4) review management, and (5) rank tracking. No single tool automates all five. theStacc automates pillars 1 and 2. Pair with Paige (reviews), Moz Local (citations), and BrightLocal (tracking) for full coverage at ~$205/month total.</div>
